<![CDATA[<div style="text-align: right;"><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); text-align: left;"><font class="Apple-style-span" style="" size="2" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="border-spacing: 5px;"><br></span></font></div><div style="text-align: left;"><font class="Apple-style-span" style="" face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><span class="Apple-style-span" style="border-spacing: 5px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Dear&nbsp;{!Contact.Salutation} {!Contact.LastName},</span></font></div><span lang="en-GB" style="text-align: start; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><font face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><div style="margin: 0px;"><span lang="en-GB"><div style="margin: 0px;"><span id="gmail-m_-315544659310906129m_-5334638735865710201docs-internal-guid-8e7e2af2-3424-7cf0-dabc-c6eb49512b3b"><br>The health and safety of your children is our top priority. In addition to taking all necessary precautions, we aim to always keep our parents well informed of anything which comes to our attention which may affect your children.<br><br>I am writing to inform you that there has been a confirmed case of hand, foot and mouth disease in a pupil in one of our Reception classes. Hand, foot and mouth disease is a contagious, viral infection which spreads if contaminated droplets or bodily fluids are transferred from an infected person. Symptoms include cold-like symptoms such as: loss of appetite, headache, fatigue, irritability, cough, a moderately high temperature, a non-itchy red rash and&nbsp;</span>painful mouth ulcers. Hand-foot-and-mouth disease may cause all of the above signs and symptoms or just a few of them. Please seek immediate medical advice and advise the school promptly if your child is unwell with any of the above symptoms.<br><br>Although this child was diagnosed in the holidays and has not been present in school, we are already taking all precautions necessary including:<br><br>- Good ventilation of classrooms and other rooms<br>- Daily cleaning and disinfection of the door handles, stair railings, toys, bathroom accessories and food utensils<br>- Early Yearsâ€™ toys thoroughly disinfected every Friday<br>- Unwell children will see the nurse and, if necessary, parents will be contacted<br>- The children have been taught how to wash their hands by teachers<br><br>If you believe your child has hand, foot and mouth disease, please seek medical treatment, follow safety procedures at home and keep them away from school until they have recovered from the illness.<br><br>For further information about hand, foot and mouth disease, please see the link below:</div><div style="margin: 0px;"><p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.2; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 12pt; text-align: justify;"><a href="http://www.nhs.uk/conditions/Hand-foot-and-mouth-disease/Pages/Introduction.aspx" target="_blank" style="text-decoration-line: none;"><span style="text-decoration-line: underline; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">http://www.nhs.uk/conditions/<wbr><span class="gmail-il">Hand</span>-<span class="gmail-il">foot</span>-and-<span class="gmail-il">mouth</span>-disease/<wbr>Pages/Introduction.aspx</span></a></p></div></span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">Regards</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34);">BSY Admin</span></div><div style="margin: 0px;"><br></div></font></span></div><div style="text-align: left;"><p class="MsoNormal" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;"><font size="2" style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><font face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" style="">The British School Yangon</font></font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); margin-right: 0px; margin-left: 0px;"><font face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" style="background-color: rgb(255, 